⚠️ 4. TRANSITIVE DEPENDENCIES
❓ Q: What is filelock?

Answer: Transitive dependency

👉 Installed automatically by other packages (e.g. pip install torch)

🧠 5. MODEL FILE SECURITY
❓ Q: What allows model files to execute code when loaded?

Answer: Serialized objects (pickle-based formats)

📁 Risky formats
.pkl
.pt
.bin
✅ Safe format
.safetensors
🧪 6. AI SUPPLY CHAIN PARADIGMS
📥 Download Paradigm
You download model files locally
You trust file integrity
Full control but high risk
🌐 API Paradigm
You call hosted models
No file access
Hidden trust in provider
❓ Q: Dominant format for local LLMs?

Answer: .gguf

🧱 7. ATTACK LAYERS
Layer 1: Model Layer
Backdoored weights
Serialized code execution
Architecture manipulation
Layer 2: Dependency Layer
Malicious packages
Typosquatting
pip confusion attacks
Layer 3: Data Layer
Poisoned datasets
Even 0.1% manipulation = backdoor
Layer 4: Infrastructure Layer
CI/CD compromise
Repo takeover
Credential theft
❓ Questions

Q: Pickle attacks occur at which layer?
👉 Model layer

Q: SafeTensors eliminates which attack type?
👉 Serialization-level attacks

Q: Dataset poisoning belongs to which layer?
👉 Data layer

